This paper introduces LX-SenseAnnotator, a user-friendly interface tool for manual word sense annotation. The demonstration will show how input texts are loaded by the tool, the options available to the annotator for displaying and browsing texts, and how word senses are displayed and manually assigned. The ï¬‚exibility of LX-SenseAnnotator, including the support of a variety of languages and the handling of pre-processed texts with different tagsets, will also be addressed